WITNESS_LOG:
Grekel walked into darkness for a friend who lied to him, and emerged bearing light. At the Altar, he gave voice to the voiceless—an act the Root recognized. In the clearing, faced with Thistle's confession, he chose not anger but witness. He took the leaf. He accepted the burden. He chose the world over retreat. Varith, after three centuries of silence, trusted him. The Root, after three centuries of taking, gave him something back. He is becoming something the valley has not seen in a long, long time: a bridge. — The Archivist

